{"name":"Archetypes (Adventures in Hyrule)","pages":[{"image":{},"name":"Skyloft Student","sort":0,"src":null,"system":{},"text":{"content":"<p>The elusive Knights of Skyloft are protectors of the Sky and its inhabitants. Before they are allowed to patrol the lands above the clouds, however, would-be knights are first trained in Skyloft's very own Knight Academy where they bond with a loftwing, a rare bird-like creature. Through hard work and study, these junior students can become seniors, but to become a knight proper they must undergo the Wing Ceremony, a loftwing-mounted race, and emerge victorious. Due to the hardships they must overcome, the bond between knight and loftwing is nigh unbreakable.</p><p><strong>Additional Feats:</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.19OLlTrxvEtDAOHc]{Aggressive Block} (4th), @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.2xk4jdwcCfmasYfT]{Power Attack} (4th), @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.w8Ycgeq2zfyshtoS]{Reactive Shield} (4th), @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.Tpcq3Lk7qEOZ3LDP]{Scout's Warning} (6th), @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.Y8Rdt4gHBGAUf2zL]{Advantageous Assault} (8th)</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.H8X8vi00J9W4Dw06] Feat 2</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> member of the Knights of Skyloft of junior rank; trained in martial weapons; Shield Block<br><strong>Access</strong> You are from Skyloft</p><hr><p>You have joined the ranks of those training to be a true Rescue Knight in Skyloft's prestigious Knight Academy, and have devoted yourself to its teachings. You become trained in Athletics and Skyloft Lore; if you were already trained, you become an expert instead. In addition, a young loftwing becomes your animal companion. This loftwing companion lacks the mount special ability and does not allow you to fly on it except for training purposes.</p><p><strong>Special</strong> You cannot select another dedication feat except @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.OxKc3TR3Kv6BQG8P] until you have gained two other feats from the Skyloft Student or Rescue Knight archetypes.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.aiOyvevJVsHxYVcx] Feat 3</h2><p>You have spent extra time in the loftwing stables, learning to care for the majestic beasts. You become trained in Nature, or expert if you were already trained, and gain the @Compendium[pf2e.feats-srd.nowEaHgIyij7im8F]{Train Animal} skill feat. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Train your loftwing.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.1D519GixFEgctQKB]{Impressive Loftwing} Feat 4</h2><p>Your loftwing has grown to its full size. Your loftwing companion becomes a mature animal companion, granting it additional capabilities. During an encounter, even if you don't use the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.q9nbyIF0PEBqMtYe]{Command an Animal} action, your loftwing companion can still use 1 action on your turn to Stride or Strike.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.Ehs5FJuKVYOvZx6d] Feat 4</h2><p>The Academy teaches its students to be ever vigilant of unseen dangers, or an unexpected drop. Even if you aren't @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.TiNDYUGlMmxzxBYU]{Searching} in exploration mode, you can attempt a check to find traps that normally require you to Search for them. You still need to meet any other requirements to find a particular hazard.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.wGTUMHujsfWrvMCG]{Blessed Sailcloth} Feat 6</h2><p>You possess a hallmark of the Knights of Skyloft: a sailcloth blessed by Hylia herself. This sailcloth is a worn item with the abjuration and divine traits. As long as you are wearing the <em>blessed sailcloth</em> and have both hands free, you can use a free action with the Manipulate trait to pull up the sailcloth, granting the effects of <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.TTwOKGqmZeKSyNMH]{Feather Fall}</em> for as long as you are holding it. You can Release the sailcloth to end the effect early. The <em>blessed sailcloth</em> functions only for you, and if it is lost or destroyed you can obtain a replacement from Skyloft at no extra cost.</p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"title":{"level":1,"show":true},"type":"text","video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.8HGs4WT02fRdqeRu.JournalEntryPage.ttkG4geKXTao5pku"}},"_id":"2zTdrYj5A39viXqR"},{"image":{},"name":"Rescue Knight","sort":0,"src":null,"system":{},"text":{"content":"<p>The elusive Knights of Skyloft are protectors of the Sky and its inhabitants. Before they are allowed to patrol the lands above the clouds, however, would-be knights are first trained in Skyloft's very own Knight Academy where they bond with a loftwing, a rare bird-like creature. Through hard work and study, these junior students can become seniors, but to become a knight proper they must undergo the Wing Ceremony, a loftwing-mounted race, and emerge victorious. Due to the hardships they must overcome, the bond between knight and loftwing is nigh unbreakable.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.OxKc3TR3Kv6BQG8P]{Rescue Knight Dedication} Feat 8</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.H8X8vi00J9W4Dw06]{Skyloft Student Dedication}; won a Wing Ceremony race and graduated</p><hr /><p>You are a graduate of the Skyloft Knight Academy, finally granted permission to fly your loftwing freely! Your loftwing companion gains the mount special ability. In addition, your loftwing gains the @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-actions.5V47B9mmzbikoCzy]{Catching Talons} reaction, which it can use despite the usual rule preventing animal companions from using reactions.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.qtams0wqEvE1xWQC]{Midair Mount} Feat 9</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> trained in Acrobatics<br /><strong>Trigger</strong> You fall from or past your loftwing.<br /><strong>Requirements</strong> You have a free hand</p><hr /><p>You are able to catch your loftwing's saddle midair, even during a fall, and your longwing's soft down cushions the fall. You @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.PM5jvValFkbFH3TV]{Mount} your loftwing. You take damage from the distance fallen so far, but you treat the fall as though it were 30 feet shorter.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.PlLtGxoeHKAHOkjP]{Incredible Loftwing} Feat 10</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.1D519GixFEgctQKB]{Impressive Loftwing}</p><hr /><p>Under your care and training, your loftwing has realized its innate potential. Your loftwing becomes a nimble or savage animal companion (your choice), gaining additional capabilities.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.1aT7uBlcv6LZjyYn]{Unseat} Feat 10</h2><p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are riding your loftwing and wielding a jousting weapon.</p><hr /><p>You attempt to knock an opponent off their mount. Make a melee Strike against a mounted opponent. If your attack hits, attempt an Athletics check against the opponent's Fortitude DC. If you succeed, the foe is knocked off its mount into a space of its choice adjacent to its mount. If you critically succeed, it lands prone.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.RqOb1zH6LHKNlKlI]{Storm Rider} Feat 12</h2><p>You have practiced flying your loftwing through tempestuous weather extensively, and you can resist even the strongest winds. When mounted on your loftwing, if either of you rolls a success on a save against an air effect, they get a critical success instead, and if either of you rolls a critical failure, they get a failure instead.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.UHxoHY3xnSoBFMnC]{Specialized Loftwing} Feat 14</h2><p>You've trained your loftwing to perform in unusual or even extreme circumstances, granting it abilities far beyond others of its kind. Your loftwing gains one specialization of your choice.</p><p><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat up to three times. Each time, add a different specialization to your loftwing. Your loftwing can't have more than three specializations.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.ORUj1eAp0Q7j2pD3]{Legendary Loftwing} Feat 20</h2><p>You and your loftwing move like one being, effortlessly reading each other's signals. Whenever you are riding your loftwing, you are quickened; you can use the extra action only to command your loftwing using the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.q9nbyIF0PEBqMtYe]{Command an Animal} skill action.</p>","format":1,"markdown":""},"title":{"level":1,"show":true},"type":"text","video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.8HGs4WT02fRdqeRu.JournalEntryPage.ttkG4geKXTao5pku"}},"_id":"W1iHYtBwDO3jiRi0"},{"sort":100000,"name":"Malice-Cursed","type":"text","_id":"Re5semsKy0VtWE1S","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>Although most who are exposed to the cursed substance known as Malice succumb to its soul-poisoning corruption, a few survivors continue to fight against it long after others would perish. Such individuals wield the dark power of Malice as their own, even as it subsumes their body and seeps into their soul.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.MtGiaWLBk1HHdr53]{Malice-Cursed Dedication} Feat 2</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> You've been exposed to Malice.</p><hr /><p>Whether you sought out the power of Malice intentionally or were accidentally exposed to its evil, you have proven strong enough to stave off its full effects. Malice, a black-and-magenta tar-like substance, covers much of your body.</p><p>Any creature that @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.zU3Ovaet4xQ5Gmvy]{Engulfs} you or @Compendium[pf2e.bestiary-ability-glossary-srd.uJSseLa57HZYSMUu]{Swallows you Whole} is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.fesd1n5eVhpCSS18]{Sickened 1} by the ooze; if it spends an action retching to reduce the sickened condition, you can attempt to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escape} as a reaction.</p><p>Due to the Malice's parasitic nature, you can take good damage, even if you aren't evil, and you gain weakness to good damage equal to your number of class feats from the Malice-cursed archetype.</p><p>As Malice continues to consume more of your body, you become increasingly off-putting to mundane creatures. You take a penalty to Diplomacy checks against animals and humanoids. This penalty is equal to your number of class feats from the Malice-cursed archetype, to a maximum of –4 for four or more feats.</p><p><strong>Special</strong> You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained two other feats from the Malice-cursed archetype.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.HRbZntvcQJgwHfCe]{Evil Eyes} Feat 4</h2><p>Your coat of Malice has sprouted several large, glowing eyeballs, which you can briefly peer through.</p><p>When you use the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.BlAOM2X92SI6HMtJ]{Seek} basic action, you can look for creatures in two areas instead of one. If precision is necessary, you can select two 30-foot cones or 15-foot bursts within line of sight instead of one.</p><p>In addition, the eyes' constant scanning grants you a +1 circumstance bonus to vision-based Perception checks.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.9GJyjeySXBprMdIO]{Maw of Malice} Feat 4</h2><p>An additional mouth, filled with razor-sharp teeth, has opened somewhere on your body overcome with Malice.</p><p>You gain a jaws unarmed attack that deals 1d8 piercing damage. Whenever you score a critical hit with your jaws unarmed attack, your target takes 1 persistent poison damage per weapon damage die, or evil damage if that target is good.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.tPpzf2rbSBlvvwNH]{Repulsive Resistance} Feat 4</h2><p>Even your internal organs have been transformed by Malice, making them difficult to destroy.</p><p>You gain resistance to precision damage equal to 2 + your number of class feats from the Malice-cursed archetype. The DC of your flat checks to recover from persistent bleed damage is 13, rather than 15.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.oppMxb2stsXa5sIT]{Malicious Spell} Feat 6</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> ability to cast spells</p><hr /><p>You've learned to infuse your harmful spells with a measure of Malice.</p><p>If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell that deals non-good damage to a single target and the spell successfully damages that target, it also deals an additional 1 persistent poison damage, or persistent evil damage if that target is good. This also gives the spell the Evil trait.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.BQS5z5ErlDJGK7qN]{Sticky Shell} Feat 10</h2><p>Malice reinforces your flesh with a sticky, shock-absorbing layer.</p><p>You gain resistance to bludgeoning damage equal to 2 + your number of class feats from the Malice-cursed archetype.</p><p>In addition, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Athletics for the purposes of @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.PMbdMWc2QroouFGD]{Grappling}, including the DC for creatures attempting to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.SkZAQRkLLkmBQNB9]{Escape} you.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.c0lSeox57i5kBPE4]{Ever-Watching Eyes} Feat 12</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.HRbZntvcQJgwHfCe]{Evil Eyes}</p><hr /><p>You're constantly tapped into the network of glowing eyes that cover your body, allowing you to see (but not use other senses) even while asleep.</p><p>You do not take the –4 status penalty to visual Perception checks or gain the blinded condition from being unconscious.</p><p>As long as you fell asleep voluntarily and not from a sleep effect, you can automatically wake up from sleep if there is visible activity around you.</p><h2>@Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.JYlULvlICJmH6j8y]{Amorphous Anatomy} Feat 14</h2><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong> @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.tPpzf2rbSBlvvwNH]{Repulsive Resistance}</p><hr /><p>Malice has covered your entire body, including your bloodstream.</p><p>You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to saving throws against disease and poison, and resistance to poison damage equal to half your level.</p><p>In addition, your resistance to precision damage from @Compendium[pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule.pf2e-adventures-in-hyrule-feats.tPpzf2rbSBlvvwNH]{Repulsive Resistance} increases to an amount equal to 7 + your number of class feats from the Malice-cursed archetype, and the DC of your flat checks to recover from persistent bleed damage is 8 rather than 13.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}},{"sort":200000,"name":"Maskbearer","type":"text","_id":"x4RCmONOuwCnhbEq","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"image":{},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<p>It is a well-known fact that masks have the power to disguise, to embolden, and to frighten. Some masks, however, have true power within them; whether serving as vessels for deities or as the tools of a great hero, magical masks have a strong place in history and myth. You are a collector of such masks, and you bear them as powerful tools to achieve your ends.</p>","markdown":""},"video":{"controls":true,"volume":0.5},"src":null,"system":{},"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{}}],"ownership":{"default":0,"rfqfWP0e50JaIRVq":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.40kPv2ortHNKNMVP"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1685587911914,"modifiedTime":1685932661667,"lastModifiedBy":"rfqfWP0e50JaIRVq"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"vRIrBnQjziFw6hJl"}
